text: Bonsack may refer to: *James Albert Bonsack (1859–1924), invented in 1880 the first cigarette rolling machine *Klaus Bonsack (born 1941), East German former luger who competed during the 1960s and early 1970s *Rose Mary Hatem Bonsack, American politician who represents district 34 in the Maryland House of Delegates ==See also== *Bonsack, Virginia, unincorporated community in eastern Roanoke County, Virginia, United States
title: Bonsack
